:"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380"},"da":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Afdød","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380"},"nl":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Overleden","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380"},"en":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Deceased","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Daniell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (Galway): variant of   Daniel  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Daniel","meanings":["English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Polish, Czech, Slovak, Romanian, Jewish, Assyrian/Chaldean, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania); Breton (rarely <b>Le Daniel</b>); Hungarian (<b>Dániel</b>): from the Biblical personal name <i>Daniel</i>, Syriac (Assyrian/Chaldean) <i>Dānīʾēl</i>, Hungarian <i>Dániel</i> (from Hebrew <i>Daniyyel</i> ‘God is my judge’), borne by a major prophet in the Bible. The chief factor influencing the popularity of the personal name (and hence the frequency of the surname) was undoubtedly the dramatic story in the Book of Daniel recounting the prophet's steadfast adherence to his religious faith despite pressure and persecution from the Mesopotamian kings in whose court he served: Nebuchadnezzar, Belshazzar, and Darius. The name was also borne by a 2nd-century Christian martyr and by a 9th-century hermit, the legend of whose lives were popular among Christians during the Middle Ages. Among Orthodox Christians in Eastern Europe the name was also popular as being that of a 4th-century Persian martyr, who was venerated in the Orthodox Church. In France, this surname is most common in Brittany.","Irish (Tipperary and Waterford): shortened form of   McDaniel  , which is actually a variant of   McDonnell  , from the Gaelic form of Irish <i>Donal</i> (equivalent to Scottish <i>Donald</i>), erroneously associated with the Biblical personal name <i>Daniel</i>. See also   O'Donnell  .","Americanized or Germanized form of Slovenian <b>Danijel</b>: from the Biblical personal name <i>Danijel</i> ‘Daniel’ (see 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"Angelica","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Church Latin, from the feminine form of the Latin adjective <i>angelicus</i> ‘angelic’, or simply a Latinate elaboration of   Angela ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Angelica Daniell was born in 1310. She married sir, John Danyers , of Tabley in 1330. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1380, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380"},"fi":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380"},"fr":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Décédée","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","lifeSummary":"Lady Angelica Daniell est née en 1310. Elle a épousé sir, John Danyers , of Tabley en 1330. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1380, à l’âge de 70 ans."},"de":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–Verstorben","1310":"1310","1299":"1299","1330":"1330","1350":"1350","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","lifeSummary":"Lady Angelica Daniell wurde 1310 geboren. Sie hat 1330 sir, John Danyers , of Tabley geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1380 im Alter von 70 Jahren."},"ht":{"1310–1380":"1310–1380","1299–1370":"1299–1370","1350–Female":"1350–